<exercise checkit-seed="0007" checkit-slug="V8" checkit-title="Polynomial and matrix spaces">
    <statement>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>
Given the set
<me>\left\{ \left[\begin{array}{cc}
1 &amp; 2 \\
1 &amp; -3
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{cc}
1 &amp; 3 \\
5 &amp; -4
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{cc}
-3 &amp; -5 \\
2 &amp; 5
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{cc}
3 &amp; 8 \\
10 &amp; -8
\end{array}\right] \right\}</me>
write a statement involving a 
matrix

equation that's equivalent to each claim below.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <p>
The set of 
matrices

<em>spans</em>
<m>\mathrm{M}_{2,2}</m>

                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
The set of 
matrices

does <em>not</em> span
<m>\mathrm{M}_{2,2}</m>

                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
Explain how to determine which of these statements is true.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            <me>
\mathrm{RREF}\, \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
1 &amp; 1 &amp; -3 &amp; 3 \\
2 &amp; 3 &amp; -5 &amp; 8 \\
1 &amp; 5 &amp; 2 &amp; 10 \\
-3 &amp; -4 &amp; 5 &amp; -8
\end{array}\right] = \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
1 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; -3 \\
0 &amp; 1 &amp; 0 &amp; 3 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 &amp; -1 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right]
            </me>
        </p>
        <p>
The set
 
    
    does <em>not</em> span.
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
